# Trivy CVE suppressions for Debian bookworm base image packages.
# These are known low-severity issues with no fix available in the
# Debian 12 repos (disputed, won't-fix, or theoretical).
# Reviewed: 2026-04-08

# ── shadow 1:4.13+dfsg1-1+deb12u2 ───────────────────────────────
# Removed from api stage; kept in standalone (su needed by entrypoint).
# CVE is about /etc/login.defs reading sensitive info — not exploitable
# in a container where only the entrypoint runs su.
CVE-2007-5686

# ── nginx 1.22.1-9+deb12u4 (standalone only) ────────────────────
# Log escape-sequence injection (2009). Requires attacker-controlled
# log content rendered in a vulnerable terminal emulator.
CVE-2009-4487

# ── openssl 3.0.x / libssl3 ─────────────────────────────────────
# Theoretical cache-timing attack on DES (2010). DES is disabled
# in modern TLS configurations; Node.js statically links OpenSSL.
CVE-2010-0928

# ── glibc 2.36-9+deb12u13 ───────────────────────────────────────
# All glibc CVEs below are disputed or theoretical with no Debian fix.
CVE-2010-4756
CVE-2018-20796
CVE-2019-1010022
CVE-2019-1010023
CVE-2019-1010024
CVE-2019-1010025
CVE-2019-9192

# ── iptables 1.8.9-2 (standalone via postgres deps) ─────────────
# iptables -m limit race condition (2012). Not exploitable — iptables
# rules are not modified at runtime inside the container.
CVE-2012-2663

# ── systemd / libsystemd0 252 ───────────────────────────────────
# TOCTOU in journald (2013). systemd is not PID 1 in this container;
# only libsystemd0 is present as a transitive dependency.
CVE-2013-4392

# ── openldap / libldap 2.5.13+dfsg-5 (standalone via postgres) ──
# All three are low-severity issues in libldap used only as a
# transitive dependency. No LDAP connections are made at runtime.
CVE-2015-3276
CVE-2017-14159
CVE-2017-17740

# ── libxslt 1.1.35-1+deb12u3 ────────────────────────────────────
# Weak random number generation in XSLT keys (2015). libxslt is not
# used for cryptographic operations in this application.
CVE-2015-9019

# ── coreutils 9.1-1 ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# chown follows symlinks in recursive mode (2017). Not exploitable —
# chown -R is only called during container init on trusted paths.
CVE-2017-18018

# ── krb5 / libkrb5 1.20.1-2+deb12u4 (standalone via postgres) ──
# Integer overflow in kadm5_modify_policy (2018). kadmind is not
# running; libkrb5 is a transitive dependency only.
CVE-2018-5709

# ── gnutls28 / libgnutls30 3.7.9-2+deb12u6 (standalone only) ────
# BEAST attack (2011). Mitigated by modern TLS configurations that
# disable CBC ciphers. libgnutls30 cannot be removed — PostgreSQL's
# initdb depends on it transitively via libldap.
CVE-2011-3389

# ── libgcrypt20 1.10.1-3 ────────────────────────────────────────
# Theoretical Bleichenbacher-style attack on ElGamal (2018).
# libgcrypt is a transitive dep of libsystemd0; no ElGamal operations
# are performed by this application.
CVE-2018-6829
